ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: CB601 is a journal club for seminal papers with the PI in the room. You are able to discuss key research with their added perspective of the field. I would highly recommend this class to a fellow student.
good course but you only get out the work you put into understanding the papers; I would recommend it to anyone who's interested in becoming a physician-scientist

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: great introduction to scientific thinking anddifferent research technique; a strong background in the sciences is required to be able to get anything out of this course, however
